This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with generating sketches in vector format. It also involves the use of Deep Neural Networks (DNNs) which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. 

The paper also involves the use of Reinforcement Learning (RL) and Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) which are commonly used in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. 

The use of VAEs and GANs for generating sketches also falls under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). 

The paper also involves the use of a new metric called Ske-score which quantifies the quality of vector sketches. This falls under the sub-category of Graphics (cs.GR). 

Finally, the paper also involves the use of a Human Turing Test to validate the generated sketches, which falls under the sub-category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC).
